FBIS3-39711 "drweu035aa_94008" FBIS-WEU-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 February 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Defense Ministers Meet at Aviano To Discuss Bosnia NATO Firm on Air Strike Deadline LD2002140494 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1341 GMT 20 Feb 94 LD2002140494 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Language: Italian Article Type:BFN [Text] The deadline of the ultimatum to the Bosnian Serbs, fixed for tonight at 0100 [0000 GMT], will not be postponed, a NATO spokesman said during a summit of the defense ministers of France, the United States, the United Kingdom, the Netherlands, and Italy, which is under way at the Aviano military base. The ultimatum still stands. NATO's position has not changed and we have nothing to add to what we already said in the past few days, the spokesman said.
